l and skills training activities are aimed toward producing well educated  compassionate and caring physicians with excellent clinical skills  judgment  technical abilities and attributes of professionalism  As one progresses from junior to more advanced levels  opportunities become available for elective assignments in specialties  Many of our faculty are also engaged in research and  therefore  opportunities may be available to get involved We are particularly eager and excited to counsel  guide and assist those who want to pursue a career in any one of the many specialties under our oversight Samuel K  Appavu  MD  FACS  FRCS C  FCCM  FCCP Professor and Chair Department of Surgery Surgical Specialties Mission The primary mission of the Department of Surgery and Surgical Specialties is to provide a foundation of learning experiences and a supportive environment in which third  and fourth year medical students can acquire an understanding of basic principles of surgical diagnosis and treatment for general surgery  the surgical sub specialties  anesthesiology and emergency medicine  regardless of the discipline they may ultimately select A secondary mission is to develop research into clinical surgical care and educational methodology followed by dissemination of innovative findings  the campus  the college  the university and the community at large  this will benefit our patients who rely on our competence  capability  care  compassion and professionalism Specialties General Surgical Specialties  Surgical Specialties  Anesthesiology  Emergency Medicine Administration Chair  Samuel K  Appavu  MD  FACS  FRCS C  FCCM  FCCP Professor  CT Associate Chair  Kamana Mbekeani  MD  MBA  FACS Clinical Assistant Professor of Surgery Director of Education and Research  Jayant Radhakrishnan  MD  FACS Emeritus Professor of Surgery and Urology Recent Peer Reviewed Publications Radhakrishnan J  Chin AC  Naiditch JA  Cheng E  Yerkes E  Reynolds M  Letter to the editor regarding Fate o